{
  "texts": [
    "Nearby agents can be defined as observable agents [79], agents within a certain distance [73,76,80] or neighboring agents on a graph [83].",
    "Net [79] labels observable agents and enables communication between them.",
    "DGN [80] limits communication within 3 closest neighbors while using a distance metric to find them.",
    "Agent-Entity Graph [73] also uses distance to measure whether agents are nearby or not.",
    "As long as two agents are close to each other, they will be allowed to communicate."
  ]
}